<doc id="266395" wikidata="Q498858" url="?curid=266395" title="Maillane">
<text>Maillane (; ) is a commune in the Bouches-du-Rhône department in southern France in the former province of Provence.

==Geography==
Maillane is located north-west of Saint-Rémy-de-Provence and north-east of Tarascon.

==Population==
==People==
Maillane was the birthplace of the 19th century poet Frédéric Mistral (1904 Nobel Prize in Literature winner and founder of Felibrige).

==See also==
* Communes of the Bouches-du-Rhône department

